Table 7#7# Business Current Transfer Pay: NA
1. Equals total household contributions and contribution supplements less benefit payments and withdrawals;
that is, net business current transfer payments for defined benefit pension plans always equal zero.
2. Equals actual employer contributions plus imputed employer contributions plus actual household contributions
less pension service charges plus household pension contribution supplements; see table 7.20. All contributions
to defined benefit and defined contribution plans are considered to be from households.
3. Consists largely of losses by business due to fraud and unrecovered thefts, corporate cash prizes,
and payments from personal injury trust funds.
4. For detail, see table 3.7.
5. Prior to 1999, current transfer payments to the rest of the world are net of current transfer receipts
from the rest of the world.
6. Consists of net insurance settlements paid to the rest of the world.
7. Consists of net insurance settlements received from the rest of the world.
